                     <interp inst="t18261026-54-victim441" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , a subject of our Lord the King, and the <rs id="t18261026-54-viclabel303" type="occupation">managing director</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18261026-54-victim441 t18261026-54-viclabel303"></join> for the time being, of a certain association, or company, under the name of the Association of the County Fire-office.</p>
               <p>5th COUNT, the same as the first, but with intent to defraud the said John Thomas Barber Beaumont, a subject of our Lord the King, and one of the directors for the time being, of a certain association, or company, under the name of the Association of the County Fire-office.</p>
               <p>6th COUNT, the same as the first, but with intent to defraud 
               <persName id="t18261026-54-victim442" type="victimName">
                  James 
                  Sedgwick
               <interp inst="t18261026-54-victim442" type="surname" value="Sedgwick"></interp>
